<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title><![CDATA[Blog – Jiří Pudil]]></title><description><![CDATA[A full-stack web developer from Brno]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz</link><generator>GatsbyJS</generator><lastBuildDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2020 07:36:44 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title><![CDATA[Don't bring your own HTTP client]]></title><description><![CDATA[If you are developing a library that needs to make HTTP requests, here's how not to make it difficult for your consumers.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/do-not-bring-your-own-http-client</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/do-not-bring-your-own-http-client</guid><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2020 11:30:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Body parser middleware that has your back]]></title><description><![CDATA[If you've ever implemented an HTTP API in PHP, you probably know that there's one thing you have to do over and over and over: parse the request body and validate the resulting structure. Now that we have PSR-15, let's use a middleware for that!]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/body-parser-middleware-that-has-your-back</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/body-parser-middleware-that-has-your-back</guid><pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2020 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Don't just float, swim with the floating point]]></title><description><![CDATA[They say you should understand floating-point precision by 35.0000000000014. This post is here to help you: it discusses how floats are (im)precise and why, demonstrates the problems you inevitably encounter when doing math with floats, and presents ways to prevent those problems by using more proper data types and structures.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/dont-just-float-swim-with-the-floating-point</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/dont-just-float-swim-with-the-floating-point</guid><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jun 2019 12:45:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[The frameworkless application]]></title><description><![CDATA[There's a new buzzword on the PHP block: frameworkless. The activities of PHP communities last year made it possible to build robust applications, uniquely composed of little bits, without relying on a big framework. Let's find out how they work and if it's a good approach.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/frameworkless-application</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/frameworkless-application</guid><pubDate>Thu, 31 Jan 2019 14:55:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Keeping your dependencies up-to-date]]></title><description><![CDATA[As the business requirements grow, so does the list of dependencies. Managers ask for a new feature, you just composer-require this thing and that other thing, and wire it into the application. But how do you keep track of new features in the dependencies? Or bugfixes? Or, most importantly, security patches?!]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/keeping-your-dependencies-up-to-date</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/keeping-your-dependencies-up-to-date</guid><pubDate>Fri, 14 Sep 2018 11:25:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[What's new in Naja 1.1.0]]></title><description><![CDATA[In the course of the last few weeks, I have invested some time into Naja. You might recall my previous announcement in which I stated that there was still one big thing left to do. Well, now it is done!]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/what-is-new-in-naja-1-1-0</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/what-is-new-in-naja-1-1-0</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2017 19:08:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Naja 1.0.0 released]]></title><description><![CDATA[Almost six months ago, I have released an alpha version of a new, modern AJAX library for Nette Framework named Naja. Now, after half a year in the wild production environment, I guess the time has come for a stable version.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/naja-1-0-0-released</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/naja-1-0-0-released</guid><pubDate>Sun, 10 Sep 2017 16:50:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Clock needs an interface]]></title><description><![CDATA[Almost every application needs to work with time: if not for some greater purpose like expiring access credentials, entities usually store information about when they were created or generally when something happened. Telling time is indeed a crucial responsibility, and being able to rely on the mechanism across the whole codebase is really important. But it can get problematic.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/clock-needs-an-interface</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/clock-needs-an-interface</guid><pubDate>Tue, 23 May 2017 15:50:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nette Tester plugin for PhpStorm: 2.0.0 and beyond]]></title><description><![CDATA[A few minutes ago, I have released a total rework of my intellij-nette-tester plugin that integrates Nette Tester into PhpStorm.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/nette-tester-plugin-for-phpstorm-2-and-beyond</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/nette-tester-plugin-for-phpstorm-2-and-beyond</guid><pubDate>Sun, 21 May 2017 16:20:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Announcing three new open-source projects]]></title><description><![CDATA[I've had a really productive couple of weeks and (mostly) weekends recently. I've worked extensively on one of my side projects using modern JS stack including Webpack, faced issues here and there, and found a way to solve them. In the end, I proudly announce three new open-source packages: a modern AJAX library for Nette Framework, Neon loader for Webpack, and a library integrating the Webpack build process into Nette-powered applications.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/announcing-three-new-open-source-projects</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/announcing-three-new-open-source-projects</guid><pubDate>Mon, 27 Mar 2017 08:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Building Nette scripts with Webpack]]></title><description><![CDATA[Recently, in my bachelor's thesis, I've used extensively the whole Node.js and JavaScript ecosystem, including Webpack for bundling modules. And I love it. So there's no wonder I've tried setting it up in a classic Nette web application as well. Here goes a simple step-by-step example.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/building-nette-scripts-with-webpack</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/building-nette-scripts-with-webpack</guid><pubDate>Tue, 02 Aug 2016 18:45:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Signing commits in PhpStorm on OS X]]></title><description><![CDATA[If you host your repositories on Github, you have probably noticed they started verifying GPG signatures back in April. After half a day of pain, googling and experimenting, I came up with this definitive guide on how to set this up in PhpStorm on OS X.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/signing-commits-in-phpstorm-on-os-x</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/signing-commits-in-phpstorm-on-os-x</guid><pubDate>Sun, 29 May 2016 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bootstrap your integration testing database]]></title><description><![CDATA[Testing your application against a real database and pseudo-real data is quite a challenge. I'm going to show you how to automate the process of creating a test database with its schema and filling it with data, all with tools you might already be familiar with, including Nette Tester and Doctrine 2 along with Doctrine Migrations and Data Fixtures.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/bootstrap-your-integration-testing-database</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/bootstrap-your-integration-testing-database</guid><pubDate>Sat, 21 Nov 2015 11:30:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Gracefully degrading webfonts]]></title><description><![CDATA[Webfonts have become quite a common sight on websites. They give designers the flexibility to choose the perfect type without having to worry about the availability of the chosen fonts. But, on the other hand, they may be a real problem especially on slow connections. Luckily, there is a tool that solves this.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/gracefully-degrading-webfonts</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/gracefully-degrading-webfonts</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Sep 2015 11:15:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[CacheFactory: for better testing of cache integration]]></title><description><![CDATA[Unit testing a class that uses Nette's cache can be a pain in the you-know-what. I've found myself writing a very simple cache factory to solve this and make testing classes depending on cache a pleasing experience, so I've decided to make an extension out of it.]]></description><link>https://jiripudil.cz/blog/cachefactory-for-better-testing-of-cache-integration</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jiripudil.cz/blog/cachefactory-for-better-testing-of-cache-integration</guid><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2015 21:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>